<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I concider myself a good EQ player, I could probably play most classes without making that many misstakes, and this goes for all my friends. When we group everyone just KNOW's what to do all the time.<P>Now in pickup groups it isn't like that at all. Even at higher levels people are still breaking mez not using assist, I see people nuking the wrong targets and warriors trying to get mobs of me by attacking them.<P>Now I'm the kinda guy that doesn't say much... I feel so bad whining at people about stuff I have trouble understand how you can fail doing. I somehow get the impression that if you're level 50 and don't know how to use /assist, well then you've like retarded in reallife and you just can't help it.<P>Sometimes I just try to hint it, like 'someone's not on right target', or 'please get on the same one'. Problem is they never seem to get it. I've seen enchanters basically tell the group to **** off if mez is broken once, some enchanters even leave their groups if someone makes a misstake.<P>I on the other hand just sit there. I see the **** up and then when they **** up so bad that I can't save their silly asses, I FEEL BAD! It's like a pride thing, people just DON'T die when I'm around, so when something goes wrong, I always blame myself and log off feeling 'down'cause I couldn't save the group.<P>Personally I get insulted when someone tells me what to do in a group, and I guess that's why I don't like telling others what to do. I feel that I know my class and I sorta excpect others to know theirs.<P>Oh well, lotsa text and no point... I guess what I'm trying to say is:<P>Should I stop being so nice and tell all these morons how I feel?<P>-Aztem
</FONT>
