<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
You can do a couple things to get the point over in a higher level group, without seeming like an ass :<P>1) make a hotkey that shows what you are mezzing.<P>2) make a hotkey with a polite request to stop breaking mez. Every time mez is broken before it is supposed to, hit your hotkey.  Make it annoying, but polite.  something like :<P>"Trying to mezz (  %T  ), but mezz is being broken. "<P>Go ahead and cast your mezz spell on the mob a couple times, and each time it is broken hit your hotkey.  If your group has HALF a clue, they will notice something is breaking mezz.<P>3) Root the offending mob, and let it whack on whatever is breaking mezz, and inform your group :<P>I tried to mezz (  %T  ), but mezz was being broken so i cant.<P>If the offender is a pet ( lot of times it is ), i say " pet , please "<P>and auto repeat that message while casting color flux / shift to give the pet a chance to disengage.<P>I dont get to bent out of shape when people break mezz, unless it happens a LOT, or i die from it.  It sorta goes with using pets, and sometimes people make mistakes.  I try not to sound pompous, and still try to get my message across and it usually works.<P>Llorian<BR>55 Enchanter
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
