Yes, you're too nice.  :P<P>You gotta remember, especially in dungeons, it's a PLEASURE for groups to have an Enchanter.  I used to be the same way until I really got fed up with ignorant group members getting me killed.  If that melee over there isn't assisting and keeps breaking mez, let him deal with the mob.  Usually, if they break mez more than twice, I tell them to get off the mob or die.  They break again, I leave it to them.<P>Recently, I went on my first Hate raid.  My guild was invited to join another guild to the raid.  Little did I know that the guild inviting us was possible the most unorganized guild I'd ever have the unfortunate chance to raid with.  Three of their main Clerics had 'forgotten' to bring Peridots, so, I supplied them with a few of my extras.  And you know what?  Those Clerics got handed the gems and trinkets that dropped for reimbursement.  Three of the main tanks could NOT /assist at all.  A Necro would keep sending his pet in on mezzed mobs, summoning me or one of the other Enchanters to their deaths.  And lastly, the main puller pulled the Hand of Maestro.  Keep in mind, there were about 30 of us max, from 47-55.  Hand of Maestro is a supposedly 20 mob, when killed, spawns into a level 57+ mob, leaving us in a HUGE CR.  Needless to say, the other Enchanters and I raised holy hell after that.<P>I lost many deaths that weekend and ever since then I started taking charge.  Don't ever die if you know you don't have to.  Always remember, you can get another group if that Cleric is being too snoddy to hand you a Symbol or if that tank refuses to taunt at least twice before breaking mez.<P>Pick-up groups suck.<P>--------------------<P><B>Logix Spybreak</B><BR><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=63676" TARGET=_blank>55th Dark Elven Beguiler</A><BR>Undead Lords<P><B>Lise Auror</B><BR>23rd Human Monk<BR>Ayonae Ro
