I think you are being too nice, but I'm an a$$ when I'm in an xp group.  =)<P>Experience Group: When I join a group, I expect to take control of what mob is targetted first, who will break the mezzes, and when the mezzes should/will be broken. I consider myself good enough to be able to handle this responsibility and I feel that my taking control of this part of the group will be to everyones benefit. If a mez is broken, I let it slide the first...maybe give a tell to the person who broke. I usually don't have a problem with melee players who break mezzes, as /assist CAN screw up, etc. As far as pet classes/casters breaking mezzes, I have absolutely no tolerance for it. Even if they do not know how to /assist (God help us all...), all they have to do is look at the health to see if they have the right one targetted. I've been in groups with wizards who break mezzes 30 secs into the fight. I don't have tolerance for that. Call me an a**-hole, that's the way I play.  =)<P>Raid: /shrug, when you have 4 groups all trying to hit the same target, mezzes are gonna get broken. I don't mind dying if there is a rez nearby, I figure they (ones who broke the mezzes) are just slowing the raid down and I let the others deal with it if /tells don't work.<P>Don't forget charming the broken-mezzed mob...that works wonders.  =)<P>Keyr Aldron <Houses of Order and Chaos><BR>52nd Enchanter of Veeshan<BR>"Mezzer of Fine Mobs"
