<i>"I'd been in groups of heavy melee pulling pairs and the chanter having a hissy fit because we tanked both. It really didn't matter in that situation"</i><P>Actually it does matter. You just doubled the damage your group took ...<P>2 mob pull takes approx 1 minute to kill each mob.<P>mez one kill the other (1 minute of tanking ONE mob)<BR>kill the second one (1 more minute of tanking ONE mob)<BR>TOTAL TWO MINUTES OF TANKING ONE MOB<P>VS<BR>Tank the first mob with half your group for 2 minutes (half the group should take 2x as long to kill it) while tanking the other mob for 2 minutes as well. which is 4 MINUTES of tanking a mob.<P>Actually it's even worse then that...because likely the monk taking the damage from mob #2 takes more damage then if the warrior was doing it. Which means the cleric used more mana and you wasted the mana on a broken mez. And likely after they break the mez the mob beats on the ENCHANTER who tanks very poorly especially say in planes...<P>It always matters, don't kid yourself because it used to be YOU doing it that it was OK to break mez because you felt like it.<P>As for how to avoid it?<BR>1. leave the group<BR>2. use charm instead (I hate charm).<BR>3. ae stun<BR>4. try to explain to the offendors how you can prevent 10000dmg for 120 mana on planar mobs and the cleric has to pay 1200 mana to heal that kind of damage so tanking both is NOT efficent unless the mob is level 54+ or non-mezzable.<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=22139" TARGET=_blank>Citra Brooke-58 ENC</A><BR><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=22147" TARGET=_blank>Pilsburry Doghboy-55 CLR</A><BR><B>Veeshan</B>
