<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Just a little note on pets..<P>If you are going to group with pet-casters (which, IMO, isnt a bad thing at all), you have to take some responsibility in _assisting_ pet control.<P>Basically what this means is...the mage/necro/shaman cant back a pet off if you dont stun for him.  /pet back off, pet get hit, pet attack etc etc.  Basically this means, when you see the "calming down master" start to spam, you have to start stunning the mob...which will pretty much aggro it to you even if it is resisted, so the caster can retarget the pet.<P>This is, of course, assuming the caster isnt afraid of the /pet back off key (which he shouldnt be...backing off a pet often is 99% of pet control in a group with an enchanter).  But if he isnt you can do a couple of things..<P>1) stun and blanket, if you have it memed.<BR>or<BR>2) aggro the mob...move it away from the group, and root/slow it.  Who gives a **** if the pet takes some damage....just dont let it beat on you or the cleric for very long =D.<P>While Im all for the "everyone on one target" thing, it isnt always entirely needed.  Root is a helluva thing.  Controlling the fight as an enchanter is more than just mez this and charm that.
</FONT>
