<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I had this problem just last night.  I have a group that I regularly do exp with in the Hole.  Unfortunately, 3 of the regulars were not online.  So, we had a pickup group.  We had this blooming rogue that didn't understand the concept of assist.  My RL husband sat there and listened to me gripe under my breath for quite a while.  Finally, HE spoke up and said that he was constantly OOM because people were breaking my mezzes.  We both gave them a quick tutorial on mez/assist and the importance of them.  The rogue continued just picking his own targets.  I finally sent a tell to the group leader saying, "I'm here to ADVANCE in exp, not go backwards.  With the current trend, I will be going backwards.  Therefore, if the rogue pulls that crap one more time, I'm leaving."  The rogue did it again, and suddenly, the Hole group was without an enchanter, without a necro (the other regular), and without a cleric.  My normal groupies know that I am not anal-retentive about my mezzes, so when I do throw a hissy fit, they know that it is justified.<P>On a similar note, I know which  mobs in the Hole I can mez and which I can't.  Rocksoul is next to impossible to mez.  About 75% of the time, I can mez the golems.  We were with 5 of the regulars and a pickup from our guild.  (Following is proof that guildmates aren't always perfect)  The pick-up guildmate pulled Rocksoul, a golem, and 2 elementals.  I asked as he pulled that everyone get on Rocksoul.  When he arrived, he called a target of the golem, and refused to change his target at my request.  Needless to say, myself and the cleric died before we could evac.  When it was all over and done with, I calmly (or as calmly as I could) explained that I know my abilities better than HE ever would, and if I insist that he target one mob, he should do so without question.  If he wanted to know why, I would be happy to explain *after the fight*.<P>Guildmates can be just as clueless in some situations as pick-up people.<P>All that being said, there is a polite way to deal with mez breakers.  But if they don't respond to politeness, get rude.  If that doesn't work, leave.  It's not worth dying to protect some poor warrior's fragile ego.<P>-Shelaria Rivermist<BR>53 Enchanter<BR>Uprising<BR>Tunare Server
</FONT>
