<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Thought i'd give you all the perspective of a Rogue in his mid 30's. I prefer to hunt in dungeons myself, more action. Whenever I get the chance to get in a group with an enchanter im thrilled (usually exp flies afterwards.) I am the first to yell at anyone who breaks mez, now I know it happens on mistake at times, but only at times. Repeated breaks and they are gone if i'm leader. Being a Rogue I rely on /assist, and last thing I want is that other mob banging on my fragile back while im opposite that tank. I just wish I saw more chanters in areas like Cazic and Mistmoore, seems everyone (including enchanters) are captivated by the easy experience kiting in outdoor zones. Would like to see more cleric's and enchanters in dungeons. Well, to all you good hearted enchanters out there, if you don't want to complain in /g then make sure you use /tell groupleadername and let them know. <P>Rowe
