<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Hikaru Sunstryder:<BR><B>You're not a real enchanter unless you can survive pickup groups and lots of them. They can be the most challenging experiences while playing your enchanter at times.</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P><BR>Amen.<P>As far as "teaching the tank goes" I won't let them die.  It is my job to get everyone out safe.  I will let them get VERY CLOSE to dying to scare them, but I will save them when they think they're almost dead.<P>Its OK to be polite at first... But if they are a chronic fool, you have to set them straight.  If you're like me, you kinda take leadership of the group and start orchestrating whats going on.  After all, you are looking at everything that goes on...  (How many of you spin around in a 360 right after you stabalize a pull?  heh).  Its our nature, I guess.  However, if they insist on being foolish, then you have to lay down the law.<P>Groups love us.  When a Chanter joins the group, people get excited 'cuz they know that everything is gonna be ok.   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  If some stupid Necro or Tank is going to destroy that dream, then leave - you can find another group... AND its not worth dying for.  Would you take a nuke for a Necro?  I wouldn't.<P>On the flip side, If I love my group, I'll be the last one out.  Its my duty to see that everyone lives...  And if I die for the good of a good group, then so be it.<P>- Zerath<BR>Lanys T'vyl
